  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (environmental gap variant)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Validation activities were conducted in a controlled laboratory environment at 22°C and atmospheric pressure; the deployed CPB system operates in an OR environment subject to temperature drift (18–26°C), fluctuating electromagnetic interference from electrosurgical units and imaging equipment, and variable ambient pressure at altitude-capable facilities. Only a single temperature condition was explored in sensitivity testing; humidity and EMI characterization are absent from the validation record.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/morrison-cou1-hemolysis-tolerance",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/morrison-cou1-cfd-hemolysis-rh",
